{"session_id":"svc-1778342401358465352","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-09T16:00:03.378682543Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-15a51f8c-20260509T155954-efde06a9","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260509T155954-efde06a9/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260509T155954-efde06a9/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260509T155954-efde06a9/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260509T155954-efde06a9/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260509T155954-efde06a9/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-15a51f8c\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ebead/reconcile: align with amended TD-031 reconcile-close invariant\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  After TD-031 §5 declares reconcile-close a distinct meta-close that\u0026#xA;  intentionally bypasses ClosureGate (sister bead, doc-only), the production\u0026#xA;  code at the two relevant call sites must reference the amended invariant\u0026#xA;  inline so the spec/code linkage is observable to future readers and to\u0026#xA;  alignment-review tooling. Today both sites are silent about why one\u0026#xA;  transition path uses the gate and the other does not.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/store.go:471 in Create assigns b.Status = DefaultStatus\u0026#xA;    directly without going through transitionLifecycleInPlace. This is the\u0026#xA;    single legitimate exception to the \u0026#34;all status writes go through the\u0026#xA;    transition gate\u0026#34; rule and is not documented at the assignment.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/reconcile.go:236-242 calls UpdateWithLifecycleStatus\u0026#xA;    (StatusClosed, ManualClose=true, ...) without referencing TD-031 or\u0026#xA;    explaining why ClosureGate is skipped.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/store.go:1245 invokes ClosureGate inside closeWithEvidence\u0026#xA;    but does not state that reconcile-close is the documented bypass.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - Add a one-line comment at cli/internal/bead/store.go:471 noting that\u0026#xA;    Create is the lone status write that does not go through\u0026#xA;    transitionLifecycleInPlace (creation is not a transition; reference TD-031\u0026#xA;    §3 transition matrix).\u0026#xA;  - Add a 2-3 line comment at cli/internal/bead/reconcile.go:236 quoting the\u0026#xA;    amended TD-031 §5 invariant: reconcile-close is a meta-close that\u0026#xA;    intentionally bypasses ClosureGate because the bead has no execution\u0026#xA;    session; dependency closures supply transitive evidence.\u0026#xA;  - Add a 1-2 line comment at cli/internal/bead/store.go:1245 stating that\u0026#xA;    ClosureGate guards the evidence-close path only; reconcile-close skips it\u0026#xA;    by design (per TD-031 §5).\u0026#xA;  - Add a regression test TestReconcileCloseSkipsClosureGate in\u0026#xA;    cli/internal/bead/reconcile_test.go that constructs a bead with no\u0026#xA;    session_id / closing_commit_sha, all deps closed, runs reconcile, and\u0026#xA;    asserts the bead lands in StatusClosed (proving the gate is bypassed\u0026#xA;    by design, not by accident). If a near-equivalent test already exists\u0026#xA;    in reconcile_test.go, retrofit its name and assertion instead of adding\u0026#xA;    a duplicate.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Changing reconcile.go runtime behavior. The TD-031 amendment declared\u0026#xA;    current behavior correct; this bead only documents and locks it down\u0026#xA;    with a regression test.\u0026#xA;  - Adding ClosureGate variants for reconcile.\u0026#xA;  - Refactoring the broader reconcile control flow.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;  - ddx-ca1c66ee (epic parent).\u0026#xA;  - Depends on the TD-031 amendment bead landing first (the comments quote\u0026#xA;    the amended spec text).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/internal/bead/reconcile.go:236 has a 2-3 line comment quoting the amended TD-031 §5 reconcile-close invariant and citing TD-031 by section.\u0026#xA;2. cli/internal/bead/store.go:471 has a one-line comment noting Create is the lone status write outside transitionLifecycleInPlace.\u0026#xA;3. cli/internal/bead/store.go:1245 has a 1-2 line comment stating ClosureGate guards the evidence-close path only.\u0026#xA;4. TestReconcileCloseSkipsClosureGate (or equivalently named existing test) in cli/internal/bead/reconcile_test.go asserts a bead with no session_id and no closing_commit_sha but all deps closed reaches StatusClosed via reconcile.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/bead/... green.\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:6, area:bead, area:lifecycle, kind:refactor, spec:TD-031\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-ca1c66ee\" spec-id=\"TD-031\" base-rev=\"cc8f4e5977e2a6f1998d3dede52dd2c4cbb38aad\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260509T155954-efde06a9\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"TD-031\" path=\"docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md\"\u003eTechnical Design: Bead State Machine and Naming-Role Decisions\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260509T155954-efde06a9","base_rev":"cc8f4e5977e2a6f1998d3dede52dd2c4cbb38aad","bead_id":"ddx-15a51f8c","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260509T155954-efde06a9","correlation_id":"ddx-15a51f8c:20260509T155954-efde06a9","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260509T155954-efde06a9/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"da2662f91cda1a228e054a6606277da122f5388da0d6a14e57a8339c508c787d","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-972c6f6c","worker_id":""}}}
